And I am going to show you,
in a tank, some water waves

00:39:10.875 --> 00:39:15.629
that do just this.
Now I want you to look at this

00:39:15.629 --> 00:39:20.185
point right here.
Right here we have a point of

00:39:20.185 --> 00:39:25.533
constructive interference
because we have two maxima at

00:39:25.533 --> 00:39:31.293
the same point in space.
And at this point we've got

00:39:31.293 --> 00:39:35.964
constructive interference.
So everywhere along this line

00:39:35.964 --> 00:39:40.380
here, we are going to have
constructive interference.

00:39:40.380 --> 00:39:45.391
And now I want you to look at
the difference in the distance

00:39:45.391 --> 00:39:50.402
of the waves that yield this
constructive interference along

00:39:50.402 --> 00:39:53.460
this line.
I want you to look at this

00:39:53.460 --> 00:39:57.621
green wave that is
constructively interfering with

00:39:57.621 --> 00:40:02.205
this blue wave.
This green wave has traveled

00:40:02.205 --> 00:40:07.009
out a distance r one or 2
lambda, and it is interfering

00:40:07.009 --> 00:40:11.577
with this blue wave here that
has traveled out a distance 4

00:40:11.577 --> 00:40:14.412
lambda, r two equals 4
lambda.

00:40:14.412 --> 00:40:18.587
So, the difference in the
distance traveled for all of

00:40:18.587 --> 00:40:22.603
these points that lead to
constructive interference,

00:40:22.603 --> 00:40:27.329
the difference in the distance
traveled here is r two minus r

00:40:27.329 --> 00:40:33.000
one or 4 lambda
minus 2 lambda equals 2 lambda.

00:40:33.000 --> 00:40:37.484
Does that agree with the
snapshot in your picture?

00:40:37.484 --> 00:40:40.230
Yes.
I just didn't show you the

00:40:40.230 --> 00:40:43.708
other one.
Now I want you to look here.

00:40:43.708 --> 00:40:47.735
Here is a point of constructive
interference.

00:40:47.735 --> 00:40:52.311
Here is another point of
constructive interference.

00:40:52.311 --> 00:40:57.711
Everywhere along this line we
are going to have constructive

00:40:57.711 --> 00:41:02.628
interference.
And, if we check out what the

00:41:02.628 --> 00:41:07.613
difference in the distance
traveled is between the waves

00:41:07.613 --> 00:41:11.329
that are constructively
interfering there,

00:41:11.329 --> 00:41:17.039
you are going to see that r two
minus r one is equal to 0.

00:41:17.039 --> 00:41:20.574
Now, what you would predict is

00:41:20.574 --> 00:41:25.377
we would have along this angle
some very bright spots,

00:41:25.377 --> 00:41:30.000
along this angle some very
bright spots.

00:41:30.000 --> 00:41:33.897
And along this angle some very
bright spots.

00:41:33.897 --> 00:41:39.336
And you also can see that this
is going to be symmetric about

00:41:39.336 --> 00:41:43.596
the center, so you would have
bright spots here,

00:41:43.596 --> 00:41:47.766
bright spots there.
Well, let's look at this in

00:41:47.766 --> 00:41:52.479
real life, in a water tank,
where we have plain waves

00:41:52.479 --> 00:41:57.918
coming into a barrier and then
we have two little slits right

00:41:57.918 --> 00:42:07.014
there and right there.
And what you can see is that

00:42:07.014 --> 00:42:18.614
these bright semicircles are,
in fact, the crest of the

00:42:18.614 --> 00:42:26.133
waves.
But what I want you to see is

00:42:26.133 --> 00:42:31.808
right here --
What I want you to see,

00:42:31.808 --> 00:42:34.953
is right here:
These are this bright row,

00:42:34.953 --> 00:42:38.255
here is a bright row,
here is a bright row.

00:42:38.255 --> 00:42:42.972
And in between there is kind of
just a muddy diffuse pattern.

00:42:42.972 --> 00:42:45.882
Well, this diffuse pattern is
nothing.

00:42:45.882 --> 00:42:48.869
This is a bright row.
You get the idea.

00:42:48.869 --> 00:42:53.272
You are going to have an angle
which there is going to be

00:42:53.272 --> 00:42:57.597
constructive interference,
several angles of which there

00:42:57.597 --> 00:43:02.000
is going to be constructive
interference.

00:43:02.000 --> 00:43:08.352
And in between those places
where there is constructive

00:43:08.352 --> 00:43:12.235
interference,
there is destructive

00:43:12.235 --> 00:43:17.176
interference,
and you are not going to have

00:43:17.176 --> 00:43:22.000
any light.
How does that relate to what we

00:43:22.000 --> 00:43:28.000
saw in the two-slit diffraction
experiment?

00:43:28.000 --> 00:43:32.711
Along this line we have waves
that have constructively

00:43:32.711 --> 00:43:37.333
interfered, and they
constructively interfere so that

00:43:37.333 --> 00:43:41.599
on the screen right there you
have a bright spot.

00:43:41.599 --> 00:43:46.044
And along this line,
the difference in the distance

00:43:46.044 --> 00:43:50.933
traveled by the waves that
constructively interfere is 1

00:43:50.933 --> 00:43:54.222
lambda.
And then we've got another row

00:43:54.222 --> 00:43:57.599
or another line,
points of constructive

00:43:57.599 --> 00:44:02.151
interference.
That is going to image as a

00:44:02.151 --> 00:44:05.019
bright spot.
And if you analyze that,

00:44:05.019 --> 00:44:09.958
the difference in the distance
traveled by these two waves is 2

00:44:09.958 --> 00:44:12.747
lambda.
And then we're going to have

00:44:12.747 --> 00:44:16.651
another bright spot here.
For all the constructive

00:44:16.651 --> 00:44:21.351
interference along this line,
the difference in the distance

00:44:21.351 --> 00:44:23.901
traveled is zero.
And, of course,

00:44:23.901 --> 00:44:29.000
I said before this was
symmetric around the center.

00:44:29.000 --> 00:44:35.145
And so this is what gives rise
to the different bright spots on

00:44:35.145 --> 00:44:39.705
the screen when we did the
two-slit experiment.

00:44:39.705 --> 00:44:41.886
Bright spot.
Dark spot.

00:44:41.886 --> 00:44:44.067
Bright spot.
Dark spot.

00:44:44.067 --> 00:44:48.626
The bright spots are
constructive interference.

00:44:48.626 --> 00:44:53.384
The dark spots here are
destructive interference.

00:44:53.384 --> 00:44:59.530
Now, let me just tell you that
the general condition for having

00:44:59.530 --> 00:45:05.332
these bright spots --
The general condition that has

00:45:05.332 --> 00:45:10.230
to obtain is that the difference
in the distance traveled has to

00:45:10.230 --> 00:45:13.262
be equal to N,
an integer, times lambda.

00:45:13.262 --> 00:45:16.916
This bright spot,
the difference in the distance

00:45:16.916 --> 00:45:20.337
traveled, N is 0.
We call that the zero order

00:45:20.337 --> 00:45:22.048
spot.
This bright spot,

00:45:22.048 --> 00:45:25.857
the difference in the distance
traveled is lambda,

00:45:25.857 --> 00:45:28.268
or N times lambda,
where N is 1,

00:45:28.268 --> 00:45:32.000
first order interference
feature.

00:45:32.000 --> 00:45:36.963
Here, the difference in the
distance traveled is 2 lambda,

00:45:36.963 --> 00:45:41.839
N times 2, called the second
order interference features.

00:45:41.839 --> 00:45:47.151
And the condition for that is
this, r2 minus r1 equals N times

00:45:47.151 --> 00:45:50.460
lambda. There is

00:45:50.460 --> 00:45:54.379
also a condition for destructive
interference,

00:45:54.379 --> 00:45:59.603
which I ask you to think about,
and we will talk just briefly

00:45:59.603 --> 00:46:03.890
about its origin next time.
All right.

00:46:03.890 --> 00:46:05.290
See you on Wednesday.

